    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fruits of various kinds of edible gourd, most often used for the fleshy fruits of various members of the Cucurbitaceae family, which grow as a vine. The fruit is typically large and globose to oblong, with a smooth, netted, or warty rind, and sweet pulpy flesh colored red, light green, orange, or yellowish pink.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>各種可食用葫蘆屬植物的果實，最常用來指各種蔓生的葫蘆科植物的肉果。通常大而呈球形或橢圓，具有光滑、網狀或疣狀的外皮，甜而多肉，呈紅色、淡綠、橙色或略帶黃的粉紅色。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vruchten van verschillende soorten eetbare kalebas, meestal gebruikt voor de vleesrijke vruchten van de verschillende leden van de Cucurbitaceae-familie, die groeien als een klimplant. De vrucht is meestal groot en bolvormig tot langwerpig, met een gladde, netachtige of wratachtige schil, en heeft zoet, vlezig vruchtvlees in de kleuren rood, lichtgroen, oranje of geelachtig roze.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
